  <h3>Front-end template for utilizing form data.</h3>
  Works in conjunction with tmplt_backEnd.py, which must reside in same directory as this file (tmplt_frontEnd.html) on a web server.
  <br>

  <h4>Usage: </h4>
  Enter text in the text field, click submit.
  <br>
  Your browser will use this data to form a new request to the server, triggering tmplt_backEnd.py, which will respond with a new page.
  <br><br>

  <h4>ProTips:</h4>
  <ol>
    <li>  Copy both files to your your website, verify functionality.</li>
    <li> If necessary, troubleshoot using your checklist for hosting HTML files and Python scripts on the web.</li>
    <li>  View source of both files.</li>
    <li>  Analyze closely.</li>
    <li>  Modify code and observe change incurred by each change you make.</li>
    <li>  Note anything noteworthy.</li>
  </ol>

  <br><br>

  <form name="input" method="GET" action="tmplt_backEnd.py">
    <br>
    text input prompt: <input type="text" name="txt01">
    <br>
    <input type="submit" value="Submit">
  </form>

</body>
</html>
